	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002342_0001"/><!--pb/@n='94r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Burnbank Road</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hamilton</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">20 June 1865 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Alington</persName></p>
<lb/><p>A telegram with 
<lb/>the news of my 
<lb/>mothers death on 
<lb/>Sunday 18<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> called 
<lb/>me away from <placeName>Oxford</placeName>- and by 
<lb/>travelling all 
<lb/>night I got to <placeName>Hamilton</placeName> at 8 this 
<lb/>morning. I found 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002342_0002"/><!--pb/@n='94v'-->
<lb/>your letter here &amp; 
<lb/>thank you for 
<lb/>your kind present.<note place="marginleft" anchored="true"><!--added in another hand in pencil -->a patent hammock</note>
<lb/>I shall value it 
<lb/>the more on account 
<lb/>of the kind good 
<lb/>will with which 
<lb/>it is presented<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>My mother of 
<lb/>whom you kindly 
<lb/>speak was better 
<lb/>when I left to go 
<lb/>to <placeName>Oxford</placeName> &amp; continued 
<lb/>so till quite near 
<lb/>the closing scene - 
<lb/>On being told her saviour 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002342_0003"/><!--pb/@n='95r'-->
<lb/>seemed welcoming for her 
<lb/>she expressed humble 
<lb/>trust in Jesus - gave 
<lb/>her last look to my 
<lb/>little girl &amp; saying 
<lb/>"bonny wee lassie" 
<lb/>fell asleep in him. 
<lb/>Another I hope of 
<lb/>those for whom 
<lb/>we give thanks. 
<lb/>You must excuse 
<lb/>my referring to 
<lb/>what is at present 
<lb/>uppermost in 
<lb/>my thoughts. </p>
<lb/><p>I met your 
<lb/>friend - probably 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002342_0004"/><!--pb/@n='95v'-->
<lb/>school fellow. <persName>Reid</persName>, 
<lb/>I think is the name - 
<lb/>but I was introduced 
<lb/>to so many that 
<lb/>I forgot names - </p>
<lb/><p>I am glad to hear 
<lb/>of <persName>Captain Gardner's</persName>
<lb/>safe arrival - 
<lb/>And am ever 
<lb/>Affectionately Yours </p>
<lb/><p><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
			
